<h1>Gergely Imreh</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="https://gergely.imreh.net/now">gergely.imreh.net/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Taipei

Taiwan
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Physicist-at-large; co-founder of Taipei Hackerspace, Ignite Taipei; marketing at VIA Technologies
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I create things to discover.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I want to make the world more usable, and create tools to empower myself and other people to do more than they could do the day before.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
Other people's "stupid" is exactly what I do too, just seen from the outside rather than from the inside. Really knowing this makes all the difference between going mad because of dealing with people, and having a tractable (even if not simple) situation.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Invitation to a Beheading by Vladimir Nabokov
</p>

